---
layout: article.liquid
title: Relationships
desc: A graph of character relationships!
widepage: true
parent: Characters
eleventyNavigation:
  order: 3
---
<style>
#wrapper {
  border: 12px solid var(--box);
  border-radius: 2em;
  max-width: 100%;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  overflow: hidden;
  position: relative;
}
#graph {
  background-color: var(--bg);
}
#fullscreen {
  position: absolute;
  top: .5em;
  right: .5em;
  background-color: var(--box);
  padding: .5em;
  display: flex;
}
</style>
<p>No idea why I did this but it was fun.</p>
<p>Try hovering over things, zooming and panning! Clicking on them leads to their profiles!</p>
<section id="focus">
  <details class="callout" open>
    <summary class="callout-title">
      <div class="callout-title-icon">{% lucide 'circle-question-mark' %}</div>
      <div class="callout-title-inner">How to use?</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="callout-content">
      <p>Here you can focus on one character and the characters surrounding them. Don't drag the slider too quickly, or the thing will start to lag because my code is completely unoptimized! Yay!</p>
      <p>"Minor relationships" are relationships with no text description. Do note that I just forget (or don't know how to yet) write descriptions for some relationships so it's not that accurate. (If you spam the button the graph spins around.)</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <div class="flex-around graybox" style="margin: 2em 0">
    <p style="margin: 0;">Focus on: <select id="chInput" name="ch" value="none">
      <option value="none">None</option>
      {% for ch in characters %}
        <option value="{{ ch.name }}">{{ ch.name }}</option>
      {% endfor %}
    </select></p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">Depth <span id="depth">1</span>: <input id="depthInput" type="range" min="1" max="5" value="1"/></p>
    <label for="hide-minor"><input type="checkbox" id="hide-minor"/> Hide minor relationships</label>
  </div>
  <p style="text-align: center;">Displaying <span id="chNum"></span> with <span id="linkNum"></span> between them.</p>
</section>
<div id="wrapper">
  <button id="fullscreen" title="Fullscreen mode" onclick="document.getElementById('graph').requestFullscreen()">{% lucide 'maximize-2' %}</button>
  <svg id="graph"></svg>
</div>
<p>Interested in how the characters are connected? See the <a href="/fun/steps/">Steps Calculator</a>!</p>
<hr/>
